I would also mention all of the staff in our Senate offices who perform miracles and put up with all of our funny ways; the procedure office; parliamentary printing;

 Hansard

, particularly you, Malcolm, here on your last evening before your retirement; the Sound and Vision Office; PISO; all of the attendants who are always so cheerful to us, regardless of what we get up to; Senate transport, Bruce and Kearen, who always look after us so very well; and all of the drivers, the caterers and the cleaners who have had to put up with so much in these last few months—a couple of attacks of Bogong moths and all of that—in keeping the place looking tidy; the maintenance workers; the electricians; the plumbers;

 and the painters. Every one of them, as has been said in previous contributions, in their own way make a great contribution to ensuring one of the greatest democratic institutions on planet earth ticks from day to day.
